quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  3,10,"Verily, their wealth shall not help the faithless, nor their children, against Allah at all; they will be fuel for the fire"
  3,11,"As was the case with Pharaoh´s people and their predecessors: they said Our signs were lies, and Allah seized them for their sins, for Allah is severe in punishment"
  3,12,"Say to those who disbelieve, \"Soon you shall be overcome and driven together to Hell, an evil bed will it be"
  3,13,"You already have had a sign in the two parties who met (at the battle of Badr); one party fighting in the way of Allah, the other disbelieving; these saw, with their very eyes, twice the number as themselves. Thus Allah strengthens with His help tho"
  3,14,"Beautiful unto men is the life of lust for women, and children, and heaps of hoarded gold and silver, and of horses well bred, and cattle, and well tilled land; these are the comforts for the life of this world; but Allah, with Him is the more excellent r"
  3,15,"Say, \"But shall we tell you of a better thing than this?\" For the righteous are Gardens with their Lord, beneath which rivers flow; they shall dwell therein for ever, and pure companions and grace from Allah; for all His servants are in Allah&ac"
  3,16,"Those who say, \"Lord, we do, indeed, believe. Forgive you our sins and keep us from the torment of the fire"
  3,17,"Those who show patient, firmness and self-control, the truthful in word and deed, the devout in worship, and those who spend, and pray for forgiveness at dawn"
  3,18,"Allah, Himself, bears witness that there is no God but He, and so do the angels, and those possessed of knowledge, maintaining His creation in justice. There is no God but He, the Mighty, the Wise"
  3,19,"Verily, (the true) religion in Allah´s sight is The Surrender (to His will, i.e. Islam), and those to whom the Book was given formerly disagreed not until after knowledge came to them, through mutual envy. But whoever disbelieves in Allah´s re"
  3,20,"And if they dispute with you, then say, \"I have surrendered my whole self unto Allah, and so have those who follows me.\" And say to those who have been given the Book, and unto the unlearned (or unread or Gentiles), \"Have ye, too, surrender"